UPMC has made a practice of
merging with smaller hospitals across
Western Pennsylvania, and now it is
merging with Horizon Health System of
Mercer County.

Horizon’s board of trustees voted to
approve the merger on May 26. The
transaction is expected to be completed
by mid-summer.

UPMC Horizon will operate as a

separate, locally managed division of
UPMC Health System. '

J. Larry Heinike, president and
CEO of Horizon, called the merger a his-
toric step for Mercer County.

“This step assures that the residents
of our area will continue to receive the
excellent care for which Horizon is
already known, as well as new programs,
new services and improved facilities,” he
said.

Two years ago, UPMC and
Horizon signed an affiliation agreement,
under which UPMC invested money to
expand programs, facilities and services
at Horizon.

STAT MedEvac medical helicopter
service, expanded emergency facilities,
and membership in the Center for
Emergency Medicine are among those
improvements.

UPMC will provide Horizon with
expertise in research, technology and
sophisticated medical procedures as a
result of the merger. .

The 15-member UPMC network is

ranked among the top-15 academic med— ,

ical centers in the nation in terms of fed-
eral research funding.
