opium poppy, from which cocaine
and heroin are produced and

President Bill Clinton promising
$2 billion to be used to extend a
new advertising campaign through

_ 2002 for a propaganda blitz remi-

niscent of the failed “Just Say N 0”
campaign of the 1980s.

Countries with entrenched
dictatorships also took the oppor-
tunity to ask for assistance to deal
with their drug problems. The
