I couldn’t help but smirk upon hearing
a few weeks ago of certain men who had
died due to complications involving Viagra.
You probably know that Viagra is the rnira-
cle pill for men with waning wieners, and it

appears to be genuinely effective, unlike

such quack pills as Tocopheral (Would you

like the sex power of a bull?), so frequently

advertised in various smut mags. Anyway,
the report of Viagra-related deaths called to
mind the common urge to overdo a good
thing. Some men must have thought to

I themselves: “Well, if just one pill has this

effect, then imagine what ﬁve pills would
do! I could be the next John Holmes!” And
I wondered if any doctors shook their heads
as they wrote “Viagra OD” on death certiﬁ-
cates. There are more embarrassing ways to
die — a few, at least. Presumably, it would-
n’t be the ﬁrst time people died for the sake
of sex.

I’d say the most obvious human
impulse is hunger. Sex is next. In my mind,

, not enough has been said concerning the
I connection between the two. For instance,

the language of sex is dotted with food ref-

 erences —— we talk about “eating someone

