thing about his beginnings. His mother
is an artist who was a fringe hanger-on
in Andy Warhol's Factory, his father
was a jazz musician.

He had a bohemian upbringing in
Los Angeles, where he listened to near-
ly anything in sight. He started playing
in the Coffeehouses of L.A. and released
his own eclectic material on a small
label, garnering a following among the
local cappuccino and espresso set.

Soon, inﬂuential alternative station
KROQ entered the mix. It was their
push that led to a label-bidding war for
Beck, with Geffen winning out and
unleashing ”Lose1”. And of course, we
all know the success Beck earned with
Mellow Gold.

With the 1997 success, Beck shed
the tag ”one-hit wonder” from his
resmne and has become a stylish inno-
vator for the '90s. Attend his concert
tonight, you'll deﬁnitely have a story
worth telling the andkids

 

